SIMPLE: unravel
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unravel
<hw>Un*rav"el</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> (intensive) + <ets>ravel</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To disentangle; to disengage or separate the threads
of; <as>as, to <ex>unravel</ex> a stocking</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, to clear from complication or difficulty; to
unfold; to solve; <as>as, to <ex>unravel</ex> a plot</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To separate the connected or united parts of; to
throw into disorder; to confuse.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Art shall be conjured for
it, and nature all <xex>unraveled</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unravel</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Unravel
<hw>Un*rav"el</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To become unraveled, in any
sense.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unravelment</ent>⟦br⟧
